author: Inside Edition
description: On the one year anniversary of the devastating Los Angeles Fires, hardly any homes have been rebuilt. In Altadena, desperate homeowners are now turning to alternative living in the form of RVs. More than 100 Altadena residents who lost everything banded together and formed a group calling themselves the RV Homesteaders. They're living on their properties in an RV until they're able to rebuild and move back in. Inside Edition's Jim Moret spoke to resident Sheilah Kratzel.
title: Some Altadena Residents Living In RVs A Year After LA Wildfires

author: Inside Edition
description: Reality TV star Bethenny Frankel says she picked up a rash while ringing in the New Year at a hotel in St. Barths, a Caribbean island popular amongst billionaires. She says she and her daughter contracted the infection after sleeping on dirty bed sheets at the hotel. In 2016 and 2020, Inside Edition investigated how some hotels in Manhattan cleaned the sheets and towels. On Wednesday, Inside Edition showed Frankel's video to dermatologist Dr. Doris Day.
title: TV Star Bethenny Frankel Says She Got Rash From Dirty Hotel Sheets

author: Inside Edition
description: Matt Lyons says he's been sick with the flu for almost two months. The nation is in the grip of the worst flu season in 25 years. There have been a recorded 11 million cases, 120,000 hospitalizations, and 5,000 deaths. The flu seems to be hitting people harder and lasting longer. Doctors are reporting that some patients are experiencing symptoms that are a little weird. Dr. Fredrick Davis, an emergency room physician at Long Island Jewish Medical Center, spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Nation Faces Worst Flu Season in 25 Years

author: Inside Edition
description: Inside Edition's Alison Hall got help from some goats.
title: Here's One Way To Get Rid Of Your Old Christmas Tree #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A bride stopped by plastic surgeon Dr. Robert Dorfman's office in New York City for a refresh. The bride is Rachel Uchitel and back in 2009 she was known as Tiger Woods’ so-called mistress number one. Dr. Dorfman performed a non-surgical facelift. Using a CO2 laser to stimulate collagen production and reduce wrinkles. He also injected botox before applying a salmon sperm treatment. There was one more thing Uchitel wanted. Then it was time for the wedding with her groom, business Dan Donovan.
title: Rachel Uchitel Visits Plastic Surgeon Before Her Wedding

author: Inside Edition
description: Harlan Coben is one of the world's most popular mystery writers known for coming up with a twist that fans don't see coming. Now, he's turning his attention to true crime with a new series, "Harlan Coben's Final Twist" premiering Wednesday night on CBS. Coben spoke with Inside Edition's Les Trent. The first episode is about the killings of Billy Payne and Billie Jean Hayworth, parents from Tennessee. The killers spared their infant boy, who was found in the arms of his dead mother.
title: Author Harlan Coben Speaks Out About His New True Crime Series

author: Inside Edition
description: Trevor Van Camp was posing for a photo with his girlfriend, Danielle, when he got down on bended knee asking for her hand in marriage. The girlfriend gleefully nodded yes, but as her fiance pulled out the diamond ring to put it on her finger it dropped off the lighted skybridge at Boyne Mountain Ski Resort in Michigan. It was a 120-foot drop. Patrick Harper, the midnight snowmaking supervisor, heard about the ring drop, so he grabbed his metal detector and found it.
title: Man Drops Engagement Ring From 120-Foot Bridge

author: Inside Edition
description: Nine months before dentist Spencer Tepe and his wife Monique were murdered, a woman called 911 from their home, then hung up. The call is raising questions about what might have led to the murders. Spencer and Monique were found shot dead inside their home last week. Columbus police have ruled out murder-suicide. Authorities released a surveillance video of a person of interest. The dentist's brother-in-law tells Inside Edition, "I 100% know that is not Monique's voice.
title: Did Monique Tepe Call 911 Before She And Her Husband Were Murdered?

author: Inside Edition
description: High profile lawyer, Alan Jackson, has withdrawn from Nick Reiner's murder case. The move comes as Reiner faces a new court hearing Wednesday. Reiner is accused of murdering his parents, famed director Rob Reiner and wife Michelle. Inside Edition's Jim Moret was at the courthouse. Jackson is one of America's most famous defense lawyers. His most recent victory was winning the acquittal of Karen Read in connection with her boyfriend's death. Nick Reiner will now be presented by a public defender.
title: Lawyer Alan Jackson Withdraws From Nick Reiner's Murder Case

author: Inside Edition
description: Cops in Texas may have thought this pursuit came to an end when a car flipped on its side during a chase, but this suspect was determined to get away. The Nacogdoches County Sheriff’s Office says deputies attempted to make a traffic stop. While the vehicle initially pulled over, once deputies got out of their car to approach the driver, they say he sped off. A chase followed. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Suspect Kicks Out Windshield To Run From Police After Flipping Car On Its Side

author: Inside Edition
description: The Town of Ramapo Police Department got quite the surprise when they responded to a report of a suspicious masked suspect roaming the area.
title: New York Police Officer Saves Deer With Bag Over Its Head #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: People wait all year for the return of the McRib. Some customers say the sandwich is a lie, not containing actual pork rib meat, according to a class action lawsuit filed in Federal Court in Illinois. While McDonald's website doesn't specifically mention pork rib meat, the plaintiffs allege the name and marketing of the product misled them to believe they were getting premium cuts of pork, citing rib prices being higher than other cuts. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Lawsuit Against McDonald's Claims McRib Doesn't Have Any Actual Rib Meat

author: Inside Edition
description: A shadowy figure is being called a "person of interest" by Ohio police in connection with the brutal double murder of a dentist and his wife.
title: Cops Seek Person Of Interest In Murder Of Dentist And Wife #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: The 18-year veteran of the Gardena Police Department named the pup "Norm," after the street where the little dog was found.
title: Cop Adopts Trash Compactor Puppy #shorts
